.TH "ata_sff_softreset" 9 "ata_sff_softreset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_sff_softreset \- reset host port via ATA SRST
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_sff_softreset
.BI "(struct ata_link *link "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *classes "  ","
.BI "unsigned long deadline "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
ATA link to reset
.IP "classes" 12
resulting classes of attached devices
.IP "deadline" 12
deadline jiffies for the operation

Reset host port using ATA SRST.

LOCKING:
Kernel thread context (may sleep)
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno otherwise.
